docs.snippet: A day after two former football players were convicted of sexual assault, many students found it hard to square what happened with their views of the elite university....
docs.lead_paragraph: A day after two former football players were convicted of sexual assault, many students found it hard to square what happened with their views of the elite university.
docs.abstract: Two weeks of graphic trial testimony about gang rape at Vanderbilt University appear to have had muted response from student body despite fact that two football players were convicted and now face possibility of decades in prison; many seem to be concerned more about reputation of school than about discussing cultural changes that would make campus safer.

headline.main: Vanderbilt Rape Convictions Stir Dismay and Denial
headline.print_headline: Vanderbilt Rape Trial Didn’t Stir Vanderbilt

byline.contributor: Alan Blinder reported from Nashville, and Richard Pérez-Peña from New York.
byline.original: By ALAN BLINDER and RICHARD PÉREZ-PEÑA
